don''t see a setting for that.</p>\n<p>What I mean is -- I have it set so that the number of visible items is 4. On wide screens it shows all four items, and there''s a breakpoint so that narrow screens only show one item. But there is no in-between -- it goes from one to four, which means that at the medium screen widths, the four items are very squished. I would like to add additional breakpoints so it can go from 1 item, to 2 items, to 3 items, to 4.</p>\n<p>Please let me know if this is possible.</p>\n<p><strong>Answer</strong>:</p>\n<p>Please goto <a href="http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-carousel/" title="WordPress Carousel" target="_blank">http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-carousel/</a> and download the new version 2.1.  </p>\n<p>In the new version, step 3, there is a new button "Responsive Options", you can choose the responsive mode "Change the number of visible items according to the container size, keep item size unchanged". </p>\n<p>You can also change the number of visible items by using the screen size query.</p>\n<p>For example, you can change the default visible items to 4, then use screen query to change it to 3, 2, 1 according to the screen size:</p>\n<pre>\r\n{\r\n  "large": {\r\n    "screenwidth": 960,\r\n    "visibleitems": 3\r\n  },\r\n  "medium": {\r\n    "screenwidth": 800,\r\n    "visibleitems": 2\r\n  },\r\n  "mobile": {\r\n    "screenwidth": 600,\r\n    "visibleitems": 1\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n</pre>\n<p>Please note. The above screen query is a json string, the property name must be wrapped with double quotes.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/responsive-wordpress-carousel.png" class="wplightbox"><img src="http://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/responsive-wordpress-carousel-600x370.png" alt="Responsive WordPress Carousel" width="600" height="370" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1413" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:82:"http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-carousel/responsive-wordpress-carousel/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"Add mp3 download link to audio player";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:179:"http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-audio-player-tutorial/add-mp3-download-link-to-audio-player/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=add-mp3-download-link-to-audio-player";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:107:"http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-audio-player-tutorial/add-mp3-download-link-to-audio-player/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 09 Aug 2014 00:59:53 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"WonderPlugin Audio Player Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"WordPress Audio Player Tutorial";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"http://www.wonderplugin.com/?p=1395";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:391:"Question: How can I add download links to the player so my visitor can download the mp3 file? Answer: You can add download link of each audio file to the tracklist. In step 3, Options tab, click the Advanced Options &#8230; <a href="http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-audio-player-tutorial/add-mp3-download-link-to-audio-player/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"WonderPlugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1524:"<p><strong>Question</strong>:</p>\n<p>How can I add download links to the player so my visitor can download the mp3 file?</p>\n<p><strong>Answer</strong>:</p>\n<p>You can add download link of each audio file to the tracklist.</p>\n<p>In step 3, Options tab, click the Advanced Options button, then enter the following text to the Advanced Options field:</p>\n<pre class="brush: xml; title: ; notranslate">\r\ndata-tracklistitemformat=&quot;%ID%. %TITLE% &lt;span style=''position:absolute;top:0;right:0;''&gt;&lt;a href=''%AUDIOURL%'' target=''_blank''&gt;Right Click to Save&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;\r\n</pre>\n<p>In the above code, %ID%, %TITLE% and %AUDIOURL% are predefined macro variables. They will be replaced by each audio id, title and audio URL dynamically.</p>\n<p>If you directly click the link, most web browsers will open and play the mp3, rather than downloading the mp3 file.  </p>\n<p>This is the default behaviour of most web browsers, and there is no way to change that, unless you use some server side script to dynamically modify the HTTP header.</p>\n<p>To download the mp3 file, you need to ask your users to right click on the link, and select Save Link As from the context menu.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/audio-player-download.png" class="wplightbox"><img src="http://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/audio-player-download-600x459.png" alt="Audio Player with Download Link" width="600" height="459" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1398" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:103:"http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-audio-player-tutorial/add-mp3-download-link-to-audio-player/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"How to upgrade to a new version without losing existing work";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:210:"http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-plugin/how-to-upgrade-to-a-new-version-without-losing-existing-work/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-upgrade-to-a-new-version-without-losing-existing-work";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:115:"http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-plugin/how-to-upgrade-to-a-new-version-without-losing-existing-work/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 04 Aug 2014 05:34:42 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"WordPress Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"WordPress Plugin Tutorials";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"http://www.wonderplugin.com/?p=1352";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:442:"To upgrade to a new version without losing your existing work, you can take the following steps: Download the new version from our website. If you are a registered user, you can goto http://www.wonderplugin.com/members/ and download the latest version. Unzip &#8230; <a href="http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-plugin/how-to-upgrade-to-a-new-version-without-losing-existing-work/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"WonderPlugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1346:"<p>To upgrade to a new version without losing your existing work, you can take the following steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Download the new version from our website. If you are a registered user, you can goto <a style="font-style: normal;" href="http://www.wonderplugin.com/members/" target="_blank">http://www.wonderplugin.com/members/</a> and download the latest version.</li>\n<li>Unzip the new version ZIP file at local hard disk.</li>\n<li>FTP/Upload the unzipped folder to your WordPress web server, the folder <em><strong>wp-content/plugins/</strong></em>, and overwrite the existing files.</li>\n<li>Clear caches of your web browser before testing.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If you have difficulties using FTP or uploading files, you can try the following second method. <strong>This is a simpler method, but you will lose your existing work that you have done in the old version</strong>:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Delete the old version plugin from your WordPress website. To delete a plugin, goto the Plugins page, click the Deactivate link of the plugin, then click the Delete link.</li>\n<li>Install the new version.</li>\n<li>Clear caches of your web browser before testing.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If you directly install the new version without uninstall the old version firstly, you will get the error âDestination folder already existsâ, and the installation will fail.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:111:"http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-plugin/how-to-upgrade-to-a-new-version-without-losing-existing-work/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:44:"Not all audio files loading in 